==English==

===Etymology===
A compound of the words {{compound|high|brow|lang=en}}, first recorded usage in 1875. Referring to the (by that time discredited) science of phrenology, which suggested that a person of intelligence and sophistication would possess a higher brow-line than someone of lesser intelligence and sophistication.

